reviewText:
High points:  Blackberry Smoke "Workin' for MCA";  Jason Isbell "I Know a Little"
Low points:  Cheap Trick "Gimme Back My Bullets"  (EPIC fail...one of my favorite bands, but why were they even on the program?)
  Peter Frampton's attempt at a guitar solo "Call Me the Breeze"
  Charlie Daniels attempt at a guitar solo "Down South Jukin"
  Alabama's lead player's attempt at a guitar solo "Gimme Three Steps"

Props to the "house band" especially Michael Bearden on keyboards and Sonny Emory on drums who were excellent.  I expected a little more fire from guitarist Audley Freed given the reputation he's developed since his days with Cry of Love, but he was merely OK.
A Must have for all Skynnrd fans

This DVD is fabulous!!!  I felt like I was there.  To see these amazing people of such intense talent play Skynyrd songs was just unbelievable !  Hey, it goes without saying, the music of Lynyrd Skynyrd is timeless, now add even more talent, and you have a combination that wins every time!!  Highly recommend this DVD
Outstanding!!! Exceeds any expectations!! A please to watch, over and over again. Skynyrd Rocks.
Must Have for Skynyrd Fans!

I enjoyed this "blast from the past". I am 58 yrs old and went to many, many concerts in my time.  Lynyrd skynrd was and is still one of my favorites. My complaint is, with all the music legends that were there for the tribute, why did most of them change the lyrics? No one sang their tribute without changing the words. That was a disappointment. I still enjoyed it and will always, just let down.
Great DVD
Most of the musicians are pretty amazing...Nice sound
This was a gift for my brother
Loved it !! Took a while for it to ship.. But worth the wait!!
Enjoyed every song and every artist performing the music.
A must have for any Lynyrd Skynyrd fan
great blue ray!!
Good tribute by excellent artists!
Outstanding
lot  of  nice  guitar  work !
Wonderful!
It is great to hear the current band playing songs outside their narrow set list. Hearing I Need You live is a highlight, one of my all time favourite Skynyrd tracks.
I watch it over and over I liked cheap trick also as one review didn't buy it if you like Lynyrd Skynyrd !!!!
Excelent buy!!
I was so happy with it that bought two
Incredible!!

I love this DVD!  I went to the show and immediately bought this when it was available!  LS deserved to be honored and this concert did them justice, Charlie Daniels, Gregg Allman, Jason Isbell, Blackberry Smoke, Donny Van Zant, Peter Frampton, John Hiatt, Jamey Johnson - just to name a few.  Tuesday's Gone , Four Walls of Raiford, Working for the MCA are three of my favorites.  I would recommend anyone to get this DVD.  It is great entertainment to honor the best band there is.
